-- Czech Stocks: Kit Digital, CEZ Utility Move in Prague Trading
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-14T14:49:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/czech-stocks-kit-digital-new-world-resources-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 0.3 percent to 875.90 at the close in Prague, its second
day of gains.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the biggest Czech utility, fell for a
fifth day, sliding 0.4 percent to 725 koruna. Electricity for
next-year delivery in  Germany , where the company exports part of
its output, dropped 0.6 percent to 47.70 euros a megawatt-hour,
the lowest price since November 2010.  Kit Digital Inc. (KITD)   increased 1.9 percent to 77.45
koruna, taking this week’s gains to 28 percent. The producer of
software for online video earlier jumped as much as 12 percent
after it said yesterday it is meeting with potential buyers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
